5: I can't believe we milked a chimera!
8:
Apparently, the flavor of chimera
milk is highly inconsistent. You think
we got lucky?
11: Only one way to find out!
16: You mean to drink that? Now?!
24:
No, Stella. We don't need your
bowels exploding too.
33:
Today's third contender is
fresh-squeezed chimera milk! On
your mark... Get set... CHOWDOWN!
38: Oh... Oh gosh... This is PUNGENT.
45:
So... I'm taking it chimera milk is a
no-go?
50: Where have you BEEN MY WHOLE LIFE?
53:
The richness. The umami! Oh, the
CHEMISTRY this'll create! I've finally
found you, my sweet... The ULTIMATE
MILK. It... It's out of this world! It's as if
I squeezed it from the very udders of
heaven itself!
56:
Oh, I get it... It's not about how the
ingredient tastes on its own, but how
it works in the dish.
60:
Even sour fruits can be made to
taste sweet.
65:
You're right! Heating! Prepping! Just
one little thing can give rise to all
sorts of flavors!
68:
Kind travelers, we are most grateful
for your aid.
69: But... why do your companions rave?
72:
I am sorry if they have alarmed you.
But rest assured—they are not
followers of a strange cult.
75:
Forget everything you just saw and
heard. You'll feel a lot better—trust
me.
82:
No waaay! Are we really back in
Palpebra?!
85:
Who ARE you guys, even?! I can't
believe you're just out here, traveling
to different dimensions with your
town in the sky and crazy machine!
88:
That machine was a World Flipper. It
is a portal between different worlds.
92:
We're actually all from different
planets. But we came together to
get Light back to his original home.
96:
Wait, so you can travel to even more
places?
98:
Places that might have food and
monsters I've never even heard of
before?!
108:
Oh! But this is no time for
daydreaming! We've got a festival
to cook for!
111:
Thanks to you guys, we've found
almost all our ingredients. There's
just one last thing...
125:
What do you mean, no?! I thought
we had an understanding! You were
like my sous chef! How could you
betray me like this?!
128:
Look, I was cool with the chimera
milk, but eyeballs are on a whole
different level.
132:
What use do you have for eyes? Do
you mean to coat them in
chocolate?
137:
OHHH... I see. This is all a big
misunderstanding. I'm not planning
to use actual EYEBALLS.
139:
I just wanted to make candy. And
that candy is gonna BECOME the
eyes.
145:
Yep! But no more spoilers. You
wanna see my vision, you're gonna
have to wait until Valentine's.
149:
So, what are we hunting next? Either
way, you're using monster parts,
right?
154:
You betcha! Our last and biggest
contender dwells deep in the
Kaleidoscope. You know 'em, you
fear 'em, you hail 'em as the king of
all monsters... DRAGONS.
156:
Or more specifically, their blood.
Makes for some great hard candies.
160:
Blood?! That is what night-walkers
lust after! Its consumption is
unnatural!
165:
I'm gonna have to disagree with you
there. Ever heard of a blood
sausage?
168:
That blood is drained from beasts of
the field. But only a madman would
drink the blood of monsters.
172:
Light, we MILKED A CHIMERA. There's
no coming back from that. At this
point, as long as it looks fine, it's fair
game to me.
177:
Nimbus... They have poisoned your
mind!
182:
Well, if there are no more objections,
let's go take down some dragons!
